profile_positions.description:
I was part of two sub-service lines in the Tax department; Business Tax Services (BTS) and  International Taxation services (ITS).

ITS :

• analyzing tax treaties and writing tax advice on international structuring (both inbound and outbound)

• advising clients on Saudi withholding tax matters from domestic law and tax treaty perspective

• conducting tax due diligence

• assisting clients to set up new entity in the kingdom including liaising with the lawyers to provide comprehensive advice

• Advising clients on setting up most tax efficient holding company after comparison between different tax treaties;

• Advising on Human Capital queries raised by other EY offices.

BTS: 

I was also Senior-in-charge for a portfolio of 18 clients
My Client portfolio included some of the largest oil and gas companies as
well as some notable names in the field of engineering, designing and construction.

Apart from Special Assignments. My routine work included:

•	Preparation of Income tax & withholding tax returns of companies;
•	Carrying out Tax audits to ensure dis-allowances as per Law gets reported in the tax return
•	Carrying out the necessary research work and responding to clients on various tax related issues;
•	Actively participating in counseling and training of tax staff members;
•	Communicate technical tax issues clearly and concisely, avoiding vagueness;
•	Attending to client queries, delegating and reviewing work to be performed, and providing senior executives with technically correct and well-drafted opinions for final review;
•	Liaise with tax authorities and represent clients on tax related matters;
•	Responding to the tax queries raised by the tax authorities on behalf of the clients;
•	Show initiative in identifying new opportunities and solutions to optimize client's tax position;
•	Identifying the possible exposures to tax in Saudi and recommending ways to modify and / or restructure agreements so that the resulting tax incidence is minimized;
